8qvjvbYvYsA.title: Best Affordable Makeup!
8qvjvbYvYsA.description:
More Best Makeup Reviews:  https://bit.ly/mila-bu

Happy New Year 2022! I wanted to create a list of some of my most worn affordable makeup in 2021 that you can find at the drugstore. A full face of makeup that includes primer, foundation of some kind, concealer, eyebrow products, eyeshadow primer, eyeshadows, mascara, cheek products and of course lip products. Every single one of these makeup products I used on a consistent basis and compared other products that I tested to these products. 

Products I used/Mentioned:
*Primer: elf Oil Control Lotion: https://bit.ly/34qWW7H
*Foundation: L’Oreal Skin Serum (0.5-2 Very Light): https://bit.ly/3WaK3sg
*Concealer: NYX Serum Concealer (Vanilla): https://bit.ly/3VCamqO
*Concealer: Maybelline Instant Age Rewind (Fair, Light): 
- https://bit.ly/2XLvXUM
- https://milabubeautyreview.com/maybelline-instant-age-rewind-the-best-drugstore-concealer/
*Setting Powder: Maybelline Fit Me Loose Finishing Powder (Fair Light): https://bit.ly/3o489Wp
*Eyebrow: Winky Lux Micro Universal Brow Pencil: https://bit.ly/3ofVsVm
*Eyebrow Gel: NYX The Brow Glue: https://bit.ly/3qQKGbB
*Eyeshadow Primer: Milani Eyeshadow Primer: https://bit.ly/33u36Uh
*Eyeshadow Primer: Wet n Wild PhotoFocus Base:  https://bit.ly/3B6Fqnd
*Eyeshadow: elf Bite Size Palette (Truffles, Rose Water): https://bit.ly/3EhapQ0
*Gel Eyeliner: Milani Stay Put Eyeliner: https://bit.ly/2RbzN6j
*Gel Eyeliner: Revlon Vinyl Eyeliner: https://bit.ly/3I4gm4W
*Mascara Primer: L’Oreal Voluminous Primer: https://bit.ly/3pTM6md
*Mascara: Maybelline Lash Sensational: http://bit.ly/3bWGA9i
*Cream Bronzer: elf Putty Bronzer (Tan Lines): https://bit.ly/36zk592
*Bronzer: Juvia’s Place Bronzer Palette (Light): https://bit.ly/3cDRl26
*Cream Blush: Elf Putty Blush (Tahiti): https://bit.ly/30JcO6V
*Blush: Milani Powder Blush (Blossomtime Rose): https://bit.ly/3tFccYO
*Highlighter: Catrice More Than Glow Highlighter (Supreme Rose Beam): https://bit.ly/3t8Z0P8
*Lip Liner: NYX Lip Pencil (Nude Truffle): https://bit.ly/3m6z6YL
*Lip Liner: Milani Color Statement Lip Liner (04 All Natural): https://bit.ly/2SxzrXS
*Lip Gloss: Milani Keep it Full Maxxx Lip Plumper (110 Little Secret): https://bit.ly/34fPCio

*Affiliate link from RewardStyle.
FTC: not a sponsored video

first_page_comments_list.comment: Based on your previous videos I bought the Milani eyeliner as well as their blushes, highlighters, and foundation. I also bought the Maybelline mascara. I like all of it and I think I'll try those ELF eyeshadows next!

That L'oreal serum foundation is AMAZING. I have used it 2 days in a row and it looks so good and natural.
replies: I couldn’t get it to work for me ☹️ The fair shade was too light and the light shade was too dark….I would have had to keep both bottles and mix them to get my shade…I didn’t love it enough to invest $40 in it.  EVERYONE loves it…but me🥺 I hope they expand the shades!

Your glow is mesmerizing! So beautiful and I love the way you’ve always done your eyeliner. I love how thin and perfect flick

But it's just not as comparable bc you can build up sensational with alot of layers and not mess it up but with lash princess it's easy to go over board and put too much on!
I love this look. I’m seriously going to go into my collection and get rid of old stuff and then buy what you used :-)
This is hands down my favorite look you've ever done. I'm going to buy almost every product you used today!

Beautiful as always!  Thank you for the tips as well as the evaluations on how the products work for you.

I am a big fan of your content, your styling and the way you make videos 😍 You are literally my role model ✨ I started a makeup channel after learning makeup from your videos ❤️ to be honest, you are my makeup guru ❤️✨

I also agree with you for the cream bronzer, that the pot was bigger for a brush, also I think it would be a great size as their putty primer, maybe they wanted to start small on both the bronzer and blush and hopefully go as big as their putty primer

wheUpE7tpKA.title: Brooke Shields’ Five-Step Skincare Routine | Go To Bed With Me | Harper’s BAZAAR
wheUpE7tpKA.description:
Actress and model, Brooke Shields, knows the importance of a good nighttime skincare routine. Mothers often know best and Brooke Shields picked up a few tips and tricks from her mom about maintaining healthy skin—including giving yourself a mini facial while applying your serums.  If trapped on a desert island, her own “Blue Lagoon” of sorts, she would definitely bring sunscreen—but might also try to sneak a couple more skin necessities into her pouch. Watch as Brooke breaks down how she achieves her glowing skin.

is it really keeps your face moisturized.
And I usually finish
with just a regular wash cloth that I wet.
And my mother always used to say,
moisturizer and cleanser,
keeping your face clean.
She used to say soap and water,
and so I used to use bubbly soap
because I thought that that
squeaky, dry skin feeling
meant that my face was very clean.
But because of this, if
you notice, just warm water
literally took off all the makeup
and you can see how
clean it makes your face.
But it doesn't make your face feel oily,
and it doesn't dry it out,
that sort of really dry,
that kind of dry feeling
that I find some soaps do.
Sometimes I have to say I...
Okay, so I had my eyelashes dyed,
so they look like they are still dark,
but I have been known to go to sleep
with not taking my eye makeup
off, which is really bad.
But sometimes if I wear
a waterproof mascara,
I don't take the time at night,
but that's not good for you.
Although I do look at this routine now,
whereas I used to look at it as a chore
that I had to do for just,
for my work or for something,
now I look at it as really
self-care, and the ritual of it
before I go to sleep at
night is actually calming.
So you saw the first one,
which was the cleanser.
The next one is the Chebula,
which is an unbelievable
active ingredient,
and it's called Immunity Serum.
And I'm going to take this,
it's in a little dropper
also by True Botanicals.
And I'm going to put it
in my hand like this,
and then I am going to take
this Vitamin C Booster.
Now, when it's in this powder form,
it stays active and fresh a lot longer
than when it's already in a product.
So what they did was they separated it out
and then Vitamin C Booster
is really just like,
this will stay potent until
the last little drop of powder
is taken out of this jar.
So, I will put a little bit in like that.
I mix them together like that.
I mix them together.
It dissolves entirely.
You can put it in with the oil,
but I like to put it in with the serum
because I feel like it gets
a little closer to my face
or my skin, or my...
I don't know, somehow I just like,
I like the way it feels in the serum.
So I put it everywhere.
But my mom always said,
it's good to give
yourself a little facial.
Little teeny facial every night.
It doesn't get tacky or
sticky, but I can feel like,
oh, now I can feel that I
can put another product on it
because my skin is already
starting to absorb the serum.
So I just use the second
and third with the booster.
The fourth product that I'm going to use
is the Pure Radiance
Oil by True Botanicals.
And look at that color,
I love the color of that,
and the smell is just heavenly.
This Radiance Oil smells like jasmine,
it has neroli I think it is,
or neroli, and then rose.
I put that all over my face, my lips,
my nose, even on top of my eyes.
Sometimes my daytime is a little
quicker than my nighttime.
I spend a little bit more time
at night taking off my makeup
because usually it's being
out and out in the elements
all day and also I've had makeup on,
so I spend more time at night.
I see a couple of dermatologists,
one mostly for like
sunspots and for mole checks
and cancer, things like that, and Fraxel.
And then I see another
one who does like more
spot therapy and light therapy on my skin.
And I'm willing to try anything.
The last product that
I'm going to be using
is called Resurrection Radiance Eye Cream.
Now, I love an eye cream.
This one is delicious.
It's just, it's thick without
being greasy, it is...
I like to put a little bit on my hand
and I like to warm it up a little bit,
and the warmth somehow
dissipates it much more smoothly.
And I pat first like that.
And then sometimes if I'm
in the mood in the morning,
I usually take one of my little tools
and then go like that with it
'cause my eyes kind of can get puffy.
They get puffy very
easily. I have allergies.
If I was going to a desert island,
well, I would have to bring a product
that had a sunscreen in it. (chuckles)
But if I was going to
be on a desert island,
I think the thing that I would want
the most is the Radiance Oil.
Because it can be used on
my hair, it can be used...
I sometimes put it on my lips,
I definitely put it on my eyebrows
and I feel like I could
use multipurpose with it.
Although I do really love this eye cream,
I might have to sneak the eye
cream in to my little sack
that I'm taking to the island. (laughs)
There's so many trends right now
it's hard to keep track of them.
I haven't seen anything
that's really crazy.
I mean, I remember hearing that for bags
people were putting
Preparation H under their eyes.
I have not tried it, but I
guess it takes down swelling,
(laughs) so maybe I
should try it. (laughs)
That was probably the craziest,
the craziest thing that I've ever heard.
Yeah, so I feel like now my face
just feels so moisturized.
It feels like it's gotten
a little attention,
but it also feels so
clean but not dry, so.
So, that is it.
You can see how healthy and moisturized
and ready to go to bed my face is.
So, come on, let's go to bed.

replies: @Victoria Costanz tysm!!

hi! always make sure you use a primer/concealer as a base.  use a light hand and build the colors up, rather than starting out with super dark shades.  also use a blending brush that you have a bit more control with ( you don't want to use a super fluffy blending brush, especially for base transition shades).  Using a brush that you have a bit more control with will allow you to have more control over the blending and placement of the colors.  hope this helps!☺️

end just more of the paint and then 
again put it in the center of my eye

and then with my finger quickly 
tap tap tap to smooth it around

then i do it just in the center underneath do the

pat make sure it's all blended kind of pressing it

kind of blend out those lines

first_page_comments_list.comment: Oh those crayons are a look! I love them! So cute the editing 😊 and the final makeup, with that lipstick color is a vibe 💝💖💕🎀 Thanks so much for sharing 🌸🌸🌸🌸🌸🌸🌸🌸🌸🌸 Ps. Your hair’s so pretty 🤩
replies:
@Katherine Cole Tips and Tools Yes, completely in my ballpark (I’m always learning new less «formal» vocabulary from you, I love it - I absolutely adore the English language and tried to speak it - started learning it while watching cartoons and movies - even when I couldn’t read or write my own idiom yet. I only got to start learning it in school by the age of 9… and still learning new words and expressions every day).
No… haven’t bought the perfume yet, but I will. That one is a keeper!
And yes, if I can, I’ll most probably leave comments and responses on almost all of your videos 🎀 YT fails to notify me often, too… Don’t you worry about that 😊✨

I’m so bummed!!! YT didn’t tell me I had another message from you! Well I’m glad you tried it and enjoyed it. Did you purchase it then? I wore it to bed last night. It’s definitely a rich scent. Still with me this morning. A little “rich” than what I normally wear. But I can totally see how it’s in your ballpark as you like the bolder scents. Very Ava Gardner! 🥰😍🥰

Already went to try La Panthère parfum, and yes, it’s fabulous, better than many niche perfumes. Perfect longevity, moderate silage, and has a good mix and match potential. I find it on the purer, most concentrated side of a scent, unlike some  that, despite being unquestionably good (say, Alien, for instance), have a lot of “noise” resulting in a “dirty”scent where you can’t distinguish the notes like you would in a more oil concentrated fragrance, if you know what I mean… I’ll be looking forward to “ton avis”, bisous 💋💋💋💋💋💋💋

first_page_comments_list.comment: Hey there how are you?! I could't tell for watching your video if you did you like these crayons. Would you recomend them? Does they crease? Sorry for so many questions, I could't find reviews for this product that are not sponsored and since I live overseas I was contemplating on asking a friend to buy some shades for me if they worth the investiment. Thank you for your video and help ❤
replies: @Katherine Cole Tips and Tools ❤

Hi! Yes I enjoy them. The are a pretty easy application. I usually apply a shadow on top for a little lasting power. I have noticed if I apply the liquid side, it doesn’t tend to last as long. Some of the shades show up more than others in terms of the sparkle. I really like the looks so yes I like them… there are others out there that might perform a little better, but I’m glad I got them and use them a lot. The crayon side in particular.

transcript_raw.text:
hi i'm michelle of Lab Muffin Beauty 
Science chemistry phd and cosmetic chemist

today i'm going to be reviewing a bunch of korean 
skincare products i've recently tried from brands

i haven't really reviewed much before and there's 
actually some really interesting biology involved

this video is sponsored by stylekorean 
an online store that stocks a lot of

korean products which i'm sure 
no one expected from the name

like and subscribe and click the nerdification 
bell so you know when new videos go up

the first brand i'm talking about is lagom 
lagom means not too little not too much just

the right amount in swedish and that's pretty 
much what this skincare brand's approach is

their products try to give skin what it needs 
in the right amount and removing what it doesn't

need but not removing too much the main thing 
that made me really interested in lagom is

that the people behind the brand includes 
a team of 12 scientists and dermatologists

as well as one of korea's top makeup artists 
which is a combination you don't often see

i think it's really cool to get this 
broad range of input from a lot of

different experts i think you end up with 
a much more well-rounded product that way

i really love their branding and packaging as 
well their scale logo is really cute maybe i

Hi, would it be cool if you could make a basic/essential skincare routine tier list for different skintypes with $ symbols to indicate relative cost of product?
e.g.
Moisturisers
Dry Skin (Dry weather/fellow aussies)
S - Hada Labo Gokujyun ($), Nivea Product X ($$)
A - ... and so on


I think this format will be easier to digest for peeps like me ^^ as always you could put a disclaimer on what the tier list doesn't account for but it'd be nice to have a tier list that gets updated based on your personal opinion so scanning information gets easier :D
Thanks Labmuffin! You’ve got me curious about the Lagom cream. It’s definitely going on my “must buy” list
I love your scientific approach, it really makes a difference in how I choose what I put on my skin. Thank you so much for your thoughtful and insightful content

The lagom cellus deep moisture cream is something I wanna try. It's getting hotter here in the Philippines and that sounds perfect for summer. My face gets pretty oily too despite the air-conditioning in my workplace.
Love this! I’m a scientist and skincare addict, just love the content of your videos ❤️😍

Thank you for your reviews with discussion of the science behind some of the products. I have been wondering about Atopalm products for a while now and will include probably one in my next order of Korean skincare. The Lagom brand is also very interesting.  I am currently layering products to moisturize and hydrate my dry, mature skin with the complication of worsening Rosacea, so am always looking for the perfect moisturizer.
I love atopalm) and am excited when someone else points out how amazing it is 😄 really helped my sensitive dry flaky skin in the winter

Hi! Loving your videos, I know that you're on the oily prone side but your scientific approach and knowledge could be really beneficial for those who suffer from eczema or other conditions. I know that Atopalm is used for sensitive skin too, but is it suitable for atopic dermatitis?

5bW56TTH17U.title: Hince Second Skin Foundation all shades swatch | Shade recommendations , maskproof , long lasting
5bW56TTH17U.description:
Today, I”ll be introducing and showing you a face swatch of Hince’s Second Face Foundation.
So if you were looking for a foundation that is light and natural,
please stay tuned for today's video!

I hope you enjoy my video! —̳͟͞͞♥

⏱TIME LINE⏱
00:00 - Greeting
00:13 - Product info
00:59 - Application
01:17 - Coverage
02:02 - Swatch
03:52 - Shades after fixed
04:17 - Maskproof
05:15 - Long lasting
05:30 - Side thought
05:56 - Closing

#hince #hincefoundation #secondskinfoundation

transcript_raw.text: Hi everyone, it’s me Heiley.
Today, I”ll be introducing and showing you a face swatch of Hince’s Second Face Foundation.
A foundation that gives you comfortable perfection like that of your skin.
Hince’s Second Skin Foundation.
This foundation has a light and comfortable skin like texture and detailed flaw coverage
to create natural looking skin as if you were born with it.
It uses a light a light coating powder so your skin can breathe freely,
and it contains amino acid derived ingredients so that your skin feels moist and comfortable.
The fine dual cover pigment particles work to provide a natural yet perfect blemish coverage,
and it is said to be a foundation that sticks to the skin as if it seeps in, so it doesn’t feel thick.
It’s a slim fitting foundation with amazing adherence and lastingness
so it seems perfect as a mask-proof foundation.
It comes in a total of five shades, from bright rosy light to natural neutral to a warm ivory shade.
The shades seem to be bright overall.
Hince states that these shades are recommended for tones from No. 17 to 24.
Applying it directly to my face, it feels smooth and quite light.
It especially applies on very well with the brush that comes with it.
I like the fact that I can barely feel it having any thickness at all, and that my skin feels very comfortable after applying it on.
The coverage also seems to be pretty good, so I’ve been using it more often.
It provides natural and smooth looking skin and covers large-looking blemishes quite effectively.
In addition, it’s said that if you layer it on, you can see a more definite coverage, so I applied it on again.
If it had a natural feeling when applied once,
upon applying it on twice, the skin appeared more completely covered and clean.
I mentioned earlier that Hince’s Second Skin Foundation is a slim fitting foundation.
Being that it has a thin application and adequate coverage,
I figured that it would help with covering dark circles, so I tried layering it on.
It applies on nicely without creasing even on the thin skin around the eyes,
and I can see that it covers the dark circles neatly.
I also really liked this point as well
Now that I’ve briefly introduced Hince’s Second Skin Foundation.
Let me try out all the colors one by one on my face to show you how they look.
No. 17 Porcelain.
This is the brightest shade with a bright rosy color,
So I would recommend it if you like creating a slightly lively and bright looking skin.
The shade isn’t too bright, so it can be used for both No.17 and No.19
The tone goes well with cool colors.
No. 21 Ivory.
This is a warm No. 21 shade
that is slightly warm, so it gives off an overall stable tone.
It’s a shade that seems to go well for those who use Neutral No.21
so I would recommend it to those who like natural tones.
No. 22 Beige.
Beige, which is recommended as a No.22 seems to work for those who use No.23 and enjoy going for a slightly brighter look.
While the color is a bit more rosy than ivory
it’s a neutral shade that is not much red or yellow in tone
which creates a pretty looking skin tone.
No. 23 Sand.
Sand which is recommended as No.23 seems to feel slightly warmer than Beige.
It’s a stable tone that’s does not look dull
and goes well for those with No. 24 skin who prefers the bright skin tone of No.23.
No. 24 Buff.
Buff is a natural feeling neutral shade with the calmest tone
which looks suitable for No.24.
Compared to the other shades, it looks a bit orange,
which seems to create a healthier looking skin tone.
So, I’ve applied on each shade one by one to show you how they look.
As I applied them to my face, the tones seem to have slightly dropped as they fixed on.
To be exact, rather than to say that they toned-down, it was more like it was being fixed to perfectly match my skin.
Still, I think it would be best to check the tone after they’ve been fixed to better distinguish the shades more accurately.
The shades looked much too bright for those with a calm skin tone when applied at first
but after they were fixed, they look slightly different from the shades I had saw earlier.
It would be best to check to see how the tone looks after it’s been fixed when looking for a shade that suits you.
Also, I tested to see how it smears when it comes to wearing mask.
As it applies on smoothly with a silky finish,
I thought it wouldn’t smear as much as I would expect it to.
Upon testing it out, as expected, it didn’t smear much.
While some of the base do get peeled off due to scratches made from the mask itself, it wasn’t very apparent.
Normally when scratched off parts look noticeable, I’ll of course have to fix my makeup,
but as I don’t think it was too obvious personally, I didn’t feel that I had the need to fix my makeup.
Still, since there will be times when a touch up will be necessary, I tried to fix my makeup.
I find that fixing the makeup with your hands to be the cleanest and prettiest.
I was able to see it looking the same as when I first applied it without any clumping or caking.
I also tried using a cusyion puff, sponge, and brush to fix my makeup,
In the case of using a cushion puff and sponge, it actually feels like the base gets taken off.
While the exclusive brush that came with the foundation works well on the skin,
it can be a hassle to use when you’re outside.
So upon trying to fix my makeup with my hand, I felt that it was a much better option
As it seems to apply on more neatly
it is actually better to apply on the makeup with your hands when you’re doing your morning makeup.
The lastingness was pretty good.
I was able to see the smoothness of the initial application for a long time.
Maybe because this is a slim fitting foundation, but I wasn’t able to see much creasing.
In addition, there was no caking, so I was very satisfied.
Like this, I’ve completed my introduction of Hince’s Second Skin Foundation.
Overall, since it doesn’t feel too oily and has a smooth finish,
I believe that it would work well with all skin types.
But one slightly disappointment was that it can feel a slight bit dry if you’re someone with dry skin like me.
So if you have dry skin,
I recommend to moisturize your skin before using the Second Skin Foundation.
That’s it for my video today.
I hope you enjoyed this video
If you did, please press the like button.
Don’t forget to subscribe
and leave a comment.
I’ll be back with another video next time.
See you next time.
Bye!

This look has all of my favorite things, including, of course, a wing liner ;) plus Glowy skin & a nude lip. 
This look is also great for any special occasion including a wedding! 

Links below for all products used in this tutorial. 
Xoxo Nikki

hey it's jackie and welcome back to my 
channel for another iconic 60s makeup tutorial

i have done so many 60s looks and they're my 
favorite to do but in like 10 years i've never

done sophia lauren so here we are i hope you 
guys enjoy this look and i didn't use historical

historically accurate products but i did pick a 
bunch of modern products that have a very vintage

feel to them so hopefully you get some inspiration 
for new beauty products if you're looking to shop

and i hope you guys enjoy thumbs up if you do 
and subscribe for more pop culture videos and

let's get into it a big part of sofia's look in 
the arabesque shower scene is her gorgeous tan

so i've applied loving tan and dark and we 
can't forget skin care i've been loving her

before it is kind of expensive but i got hooked 
on their face oil and make sure you are just

very hydrated as well as your under eye area 
this will always help with makeup application

i recently got the armani beauty 
luminous silk hydrating primer

applying that to the skin and then i 
was planning on using the armani silk

foundation but i decided i didn't need as much 
coverage and i went with rare beauty instead

i love this foundation and a beauty 
tip from sophia loren is to have

a tan so you can skip out on foundation but 
sun damage is real so i went with a fake tan

and then to try to emulate her beautiful bone 
structure i took an og product the maybelline

age rewind concealer highlighting my chin in 
kind of a square shape as well as my jawline

and you really want to highlight the 
center of your face the ball of the
cheek up the cheekbone for a sofia inspired look

to make the contour bold but still 
seamless i'm gonna layer products

first a tiny bit of the too faced born this 
way concealer in honey and i have a video with

too faced over on their channel where i use these 
concealers so i'll have it linked in the cards and

the cheekbone shape is high through the top and 
then lower in a rounded shape towards the mouth

speaking of really cute vintage inspired products 
this is the pretty vulgar powder and it comes with

this adorable pink powder puff really fun to use 
and it sets the face really nice i used a touch of

chanel bronzer to try to blend in where i drew on 
a fuller hairline and then the kevin aquan contour

powder again building up little by little you can 
of course skip contouring steps just enhance your

own features however you like i just do this 
part for fun as a bit of a challenge to try to

look more like whoever i'm recreating but we are 
different ages i have a very round face shape so

it won't be exact but still fun to try and then 
the nose contour i like to do a little shadow

underneath when anyone has a longer nose than i 
do if you want to go more intense you can also

enhance your nostril shape but obviously this 
one is not a daily step i'm just trying to get

that iconic sofia look i really like her nose 
i think it really stands out and then with the

charlotte tilbury highlight in spotlight add to 
the cheekbones nose and chin and then brows sophia

shaved hers off and then would draw a little 
upward strokes to create a full shape my brows

are pretty full so how i'm recreating this look 
i'm gonna add a couple strokes at the front of the

brow because mine start a bit lower and that way 
you'll see some of that feathery effect but too

many of these strokes throughout my natural brows 
and they end up looking too bold so i'm brushing

them up popping in some hazel contacts that are 
appearing a bit more green over my blue eyes

and let's move on to the eye makeup first step 
you want to use white liner or if you want to

go less bold you could use a champagne shade or a 
peach and draw from the water line up towards the

tail of your drawn on brow i mainly use this 
dior palette and with the matte latest shade

back onto the brow bone and then taking the matte 
gray shade and a bit of the peach i'm blending

into the first half of the crease it's picking up 
a bit warmer and it's nice to have a slight bit of

warmth when working with grays and taupes all over 
the lid i'm using the deepest shade in the palette

and sophia would use a cream black all over the 
lid but i'm not a big fan of using cream shadows

on myself i feel like powder i just have way more 
control i prefer to build it from light to dark

so this is how i went about it taking the taupe 
and packing onto the lid and then when i get

closer to the crease i'm bringing in a bit more 
of a silvery taupe shade blending towards the wing

you want to keep the depth on the lid closer 
to the lash line and i'm not blending too far

up you want to have the brow bone appear bright 
in contrast to the deeper lid now that i have

the base shade go with a matte black shadow and 
draw a line from above your outer corner crease

in a straight line into the center of your crease 
and blend this black closer to your lash line

also add some of the matte black smoked under the 
white liner and now it's time for bold gel liner i

decided to go with this one by pretty vulgar again 
look at how cute this packaging is it totally

reminds me of harry potter and follow that white 
line again starting to build up through the center

and i found this product was really easy to 
use but i haven't seen how long the gel lasts

so if you have tried this one out let me know how 
long it's lasted you i'm gonna make sure i really

keep that lid on there with the tiny pointed 
brush creating a point in the inner corner

with more of that gel black liner accenting 
the inner tear duct and then following really

close to the bottom lash line and flicking upwards 
underneath the white liner connecting to the upper

wing with the black again i'm 
deepening up that outer corner

making sure right under the bottom wing that 
it smoked out a bit but that the black line

isn't too thick or harsh it's definitely 
heavier on the top lid than the bottom

using my favorite barbie lash curler i love barbie 
collabs and you want to get as much curl as you

can before going in with mascara this is the gucci 
mascara i use it pretty much every day layering

this on the top and bottom lashes and with the 
top lash line the middle lashes to fan upwards

and have a lot of curl i've done a couple coats 
and apply a set of outer corner lashes that start

right after the middle of the lid so you still see 
those fanned out natural lashes and then tilt the

end of the band slightly upwards following 
the gel liner and not your actual eye shape

this will extend the eye shape make them look 
wider more almond shaped while the lashes are

drying before i add more mascara let's do the 
lip shape go with the bold v and i over lined

my top lip a little bit since in my case my top 
lip is quite a bit smaller and then extend your

lip line a bit further than your bottom lip this 
to me reminds me of mila kunis for some reason

and then i'm lining my bottom lip i actually think 
they look quite a bit alike in this shot anyway

and you can go two directions with a lip look 
for the actual scenes i was watching her lips

looked very vibrant peachy pink with a gloss but 
then in still photos they looked very pale peachy

nude so i'll show both i went with sunset lover by 
charlotte tilbury because it's quite bright on me

and sophia liked to use lipstick on her cheeks 
so i decided to use the same lipstick as blush

and then a pink gloss from scott barnes 
to add more pink to the peachy lip

i'll have this towel set that i'm wearing linked 
down below from amazon and i love the bathroom in

the scenes that i'm inspired by comment bathroom 
goals is the pop culture password and keep on

watching because i wanted to share how you can 
create a retro sofia loren hairstyle to go with

this look we're not going to keep it in the 
towel and here's the second lip combo because

in the scene it definitely looks peachy pink all 
the way through but in this very famous photo her

lip looks very nude a pigmented gloss this is too 
faced lip injection glossy in the shade milkshake

and applying that to my lips my favorite nude 
lipstick is nude kate but i wanted to go with

something a bit lighter and in this version 
you're seeing because i did film this on two

separate days i deepened up the eye with more 
black liner a bit more black shadow to the lid

and now let's take off the head towel and as 
you can see i stuffed it with toilet paper

this is so it had a fuller 
appearance um like a thick towel

and let's see what we can do with this messy bun 
i found this really unique top i wish it wasn't so

short of a crop top but in arabesque she wears 
this sheer black dress that has like feathers

at the bottom and i thought the sleeves kind 
of gave the same vibe so i'll have it linked

down below if you like this top and all you got 
to do is put your hair in a super high ponytail

i fill in my hairline by the way i'll use a 
matte dark shadow and then i'm going to pull

up the top of the pony for a bit of a volume at 
the front here's the photo that i'm referencing

and this is really similar to another recent 60s 
tutorial you loop a piece of your ponytail forward

and create a bit of a pin curl pin on either 
side with bobby pins so that it stays in place

now we have all this length left over so create 
another pin curl and shorten your hair as much

as you can so that you're left with one hanging 
piece that is going to become a bang like section

i'm curling my hair with the barbie steam pod 
by revlon and i love this thing especially to

straighten my hair it's so fun to use i love that 
it's pink i have a really low setting on here so

it's not like giving it a perfect curl or anything 
but i just use a bit of heat curve it in and then

set with hairspray before creating another pin 
curl with a curved end for that front detail
there's like two curls on each side

and the rest of the style create a bit of teasing 
and create loops making sure that you pin on

either side of the loop around your head so you 
get a big fanned out bun but the pin curls lay a

bit further down to the back and sides of your 
head it could have been a french twist at the

back i'm not sure i just completed it with these 
loops and it looks like a bun up top at the front

but the sides kind of taper down so you 
don't get a distinct bun shape all around

these thrifted earrings have come in handy i 
wore them in the ariana grande rem beauty review

and i wore them in several videos now but they do 
hurt and you can always find really cute vintage

jewelry on etsy or poshmark that's my favorite and 
if you want to see more hair inspiration check out

the three heatless hairstyles with black bows that 
i did super trendy right now or if you're looking

for more of a modern makeup look check out this 
kendall jenner inspired tutorial i did last year
you

Ink The Velvet, it's their new five colors.
It's very different from the original Ink The Velvet colors, they're so moody.
I was so excited, how is it on my lips?
Pretty, right?
It doesn't feel like a cheap tint of the price of 9,000 won.
The color's so luxurious.
Like the department store lip product, right?
There are five colors,
all soft and muted colors.
The Teteum collaboration Ink The Velvet that was out a bit ago,
those two colors were pretty grey
but these are less grey, and softer.
It's a more wearable nude color.
Same with Teteum colors,
but it's more white on the lips than on my arm.
It looks like the milky nude colors.
The swatches aren't the same as the actual color on your lips.
You must all know the texture of this Ink The Velvet since it's so famous,
it's the creamy velvet tint.
The thick and creamy feel
wraps around the lips, keeping it moist, with its matte velvet texture.
There have been so many lip products at Peripera
and the most popular one is the 'Ink The~' line.
Ink The Velvet, Ink The Airy Velvet,
and their newly released ones have the name 'Ink Mood~'
Ink Mood Matte Tint, Ink Mood Drop Tint,
and Ink Mood Matte Lipstick.
This Ink Mood line goes along with the COVID life,
the texture being thinner and more fitting.
The Ink Mood Matte Tint that I reviewed last year
has that thin and fitting matte texture for that face mask life.
It doesn't get stained, it has the absorbing-in application.
Comparing it to Ink Mood Matte Tint,
Ink The Velvet is much thicker and creamier
so you may think it's only doing it on the surface.
But with the creamy velvet texture
it's much less dry, with a thicker color.
It really covers up that lip color.
It's not about which tint is good and which is bad,
it may vary with preferences.
However, since Ink The Velvet is thicker
it does get stains.
I recommend you finish it off with an mm-ah on a piece of tissue.
Ink The Velvet is a famous line for its staining ability,
but perhaps with the nude color, it's doesn't stain too much.
The stain color isn't too nude, it's pretty vivid.
Still, since the color's so thick
the stain color has not as much effect.
All the matte tints nowadays
have the thin and fitting texture, right?
So a thick texture like Ink The Velvet
felt like something new.
This product leaves a bit of a glow.
So if you want less of that glow
use your fingers and it gets more blurry.
Plus it can reduce some of the extra product
so I recommend you use your fingertip to blend it out.
Finally the fragrance, the same as that of the original Ink The Velvet.
Some sheer flowery smell.
Many people have used this Ink The Velvet
so I'm sure it's something familiar.
So let me use these moody colors on my lips
and compare the similar colors as well.
Let's go again!
First up, no.24 Milky Nude.
It's the nude beige, but not too yellow; an earl-grey beige.
It's like Mac Date Maker and Mull It Over mixed together.
Comparing it to other base lips I've been using
it's less yellow, greyer.
With a lot of white, it's a very soft beige.
It's white but not neon-like
so it's a nice moody touch.
It's a warm base with not much yellowness compared to the other base lips
so if you like a thick texture
I recommend you take one as a base lip.
This color's amazing with covering up that purple on your lips.
Mixing it with no.2 Cinnamon Nude for that soft autumn warm feel, amazing as well.
I mixed it with n.28 Mauveful Nude
for that warm-and-cool mysterious muted lip color, it was pretty too.
No.25 Cinnamon Nude is a muted rose brown color.
Looking at its swatch, it had that luxurious color
like that of Hera Rosy Suede.
This line of products gets murkier in color on the lips.
It gets softer and nuder than the swatch color.
So it has this rose milk tea color
with a drop of milk.
It's like a warm cup of earl-grey milk tea with some rose color, right?
If you're a warm tone and you're looking for one single color
I recommend you with this no.25.
It's muted, so it gets you that mood
yet it's not too deep.
No.26 Well-made Nude is
pinker than no.24 with its nude rose color.
It's like getting yellow out and rose in for Etude Midnight Mauve,
it's a cooler rose beige tone than no.24.
It's a nice base lip too.
This color has that nice mixture of white and grey
with that nice murky color.
It also has that lukewarm mauve with milk,
another pretty color it was.
No.27 Strawberry Nude
is more pink mauve than no.26.
It's something that I'd get mixing mauve colors
with YSL Nude Emblem.
You do see more whiteness on the lips, right?
This color's like white-like grey with pink.
It's a light pink, but not too saturated
so the color itself isn't too vivid.
It's light yet sheer, so I think it's a good
moody choice for the summer cool lights.
Finally no.28 Mauveful Nude.
It's a very muted grayish mauve.
It's more milk added to Mac More The Mehr-ier.
This color's much softer and nicer when applied in a thin layer.
I don't think it will look great on many
if you're not a complete mute tone,
but it's a very nice color that makes you enjoy
the 'unique and moody me' vibe.
With more layers, it gets more toned down, so it gets more unique.
I really personally loved the Mac More The Mehr-ier.
It's not the replica, but the mood is very similar
so I loved it so much.
That was my take on
Peripera's new Ink The Velvet Nude-Brew Collection.
How was it?
I thought they were so luxurious in color.
I love what I'm wearing right now as well.
It's all the trendy colors of the era.
But, if you liked that vivid color of Peripera, this will be a letdown for you.
It's something that their line didn't have before
so I loved it.
Thank you for finishing this video today.
Have a happy rest of the day and cheer up tomorrow!
Bye!

As doctor passionate about skin care that delivers results and about well-aging,  I want to help you quickly and efficiently pick a skin care regime that works, by explaining the science behind skin and by sharing quick product reviews.
I am a big believer that creating a skincare routine that targets your specific concerns is not a matter of your budget. There are many great affordable brands out there: The Inkey List, Good Molecules, Geek & Gorgeous or pixi skincare to name a few of my favorites, and if you know how to combine them, you are well on your way to healthy and happy skin.
Healthy and happy skin does not mean "flawless" - whatever that might be. I have been struggling with acne, hyperpigmentation and postinflammatory erythema (PIH and PIE) for most of my adult life, and it took me a while to figure out that gentle is key. I went through a retinol damaged skin barrier, acne flare ups and sun damage until I finally reached my happy place: With Tretinoin, sunscreen and of course a red lipstick!

transcript_raw.text:
I tend to talk about skincare that is more 
on the affordable side on this channel,

and the Zelens Power D Fortifying 
& Restoring Vitamin D Concentrate

definitely does not fall into this category.
It is part of the Zelens Vitamin Alphabet

featuring Power A to Power E, but while A, B, C 
and E are pretty common ingredients in skincare,
I have not seen Vitamin D around much.

Still the Zelens Power D has been a 
staple in my routine for five years now,

I got my first bottle back when they were 
still called Treatment Drops back in 2017,

and I figured it was about time I told you why 
I keep spending so much money on a face oil.

If you are new here, welcome! 
I am Doctor Anne, a physician
passionate about skincare and well aging.

What Zelens Power D Fortifying & 
Restoring Vitamin D Concentrate claims

A high-potency provitamin D3 concentrate 
enriched with replenishing lipids

structurally similar to those found in the skin. 
Infused with a proprietary complex of botanicals

rich in plant sterols, this unprecedented 
fortifying and restoring treatment helps

to strengthen skin’s natural barrier, build 
its resilience, and protects skin against

environmental aggressors and stressed conditions. 
Leaves skin supple, plumper and healthy-looking.

Texture and smell
While it is described as

being a dry oil on the website, I do think it is 
pretty average in oiliness. Not heavy, but still

feeling like an oil on my admittedly more oily 
skin. The scent is very faint and slightly nutty.

How to use Zelens Power D Fortifying 
& Restoring Vitamin D Concentrate

Apparently it is suitable for morning and night 
time use, but if that works for you probably

heavily depends on your skin type. As I said, I 
am normal to oily and wouldn’t dream of using it

in the mornings. For me it is a night time product 
that goes on either as last step or mixed in with

my moisturizer if I want just a little more oomph. 
My preferred way though is two drops of the oil

pressed into my face to end my evening routine.
I am not exaggerating if I say that this is my

secret weapon for flake-free 
skin using Tretinoin in winter.

Ingredients of Zelens Power D Fortifying 
& Restoring Vitamin D Concentrate

Other than the Vitamin D I will touch on in 
a bit, this concentrate contains a bunch of

different plant oils, Squalane, Aminoacids and 
soothing ingredients like Bisabolol. There are

also Phospholipids, Linoleic and Linolenic Acid 
which are essential for a healthy skin barrier.

The Vitamin D is present in form of 
7-Dehydrocholesterol, so actually Provitamin D3

that gets converted into Vitamin D 
in the skin And, just to be clear,

it will not cure any systemic Vitamin D 
deficiencies, you’d need a supplement for that.

So while it doesn’t help with bone 
density and your immune system,

it does have anti-inflammatory, antioxidant 
and calming benefits for the skin.

Now I will be completely honest here: I am 
not sure if the resilience I see in my skin

when using this during winter is due to the 
Vitamin D or due to the blend of lipids that

smooth down my skin's outer layer, but 
I really don’t care. What I care about

is that since I started incorporating this 
one into my winter skincare routine, my skin

never again was the flakey mess Tretinoin caused 
it to be as soon as the temperatures dropped.

Which skin types do I recommend it to?
I really don’t think this one is suited

to oily skin types, but if you are normal 
and prone to irritation due to Tretinoin,

or if your skin is dry and inflamed for any 
reason, this could be a game changer. And if you

shy away from the price - I get the 10 ml and they 
last me well over 6 months, which is for how long

I need it anyway, so while I know it is beyond the 
budget of many, to me it is worth repurchasing.

What is your most expensive product? 
Tell me in the comments below.

I will link to more videos you might find 
interesting on the screen and add links

to my Instagram, blog and Patreon 
account in the description box.
See you soon, bye!

j1RNzqyZnEA.description:
This look was so much fun to create and a departure from what I normally gravitate towards color wise. The colors chosen were all Cool- Tones but just a disclaimer, sometimes colors show up slightly different on camera 🎥 it may read a little more warm but trust me, in person this look was COOL all the way ;)

As always I’m using a ton of my favorite products. Specifically the dose of colors cool palette, I have been LOVING this palette lately and it’s actually what inspired this whole look. 

Don’t forget to follow me on Instagram for more makeup tutorials and inspiration 💋
Xo Nikki

first_page_comments_list.comment: I love you how you leave the blending process in your videos rather than editing them down to a couple seconds.  The education & technique are what I'm here for.  Thanks!
replies: Me too it teaches me so much.
I’m so happy to hear that because we go back and fourth when editing videos on how much to include so your feedback is super helpful. Thank you!

first_page_comments_list.comment: It is very much appreciated a cool tone look!! I can rarely see one on youtube. Plus, you look gorgeous!
replies: So glad you like this look! I agree there are not many cool tone looks on YouTube!

first_page_comments_list.comment: I just love your tutorials. I’m always looking forward to them. ❤️ You look stunning as always. 😍
She is so gorgeous. It would be a dream to have her do my makeup!!
Love this look. It’s a great reminder that you don’t have to go straight into really dark shades to have a beautifully defined eye ❤️

transcript_raw.text:
Hi everyone and welcome back to my channel, if 
you're new here my name is Gail and I create easy

to achieve makeup looks using mainly affordable 
makeup with minimal fuss! First of all I just

want to say Happy New Year! Happy 2022, I cannot 
believe we're in the new year already and today

by popular demand I'm going to start a series 
of mainly drugstore foundation reviews and in

today's video I'm going to be reviewing this 
drugstore foundation by Milani. It's the 2 in

1 Conceal and Perfect foundation. I have used 
it before so it's not a first impressions so

therefore I know how it performs on my skin. That 
being said I'm going to show you how to apply it

then I'm going to do 2 check-ins then at 
the end of the video I'm going to give you

my final thoughts on how I feel this foundation 
performs. The good the bad and the ugly! I'm not

saying it's good or bad or ugly but i'll give you 
the full low down so if you're ready let's begin!

My face is moisturized, I'm not using any primer - 
I want you to see how it looks without any primer

so just skincare is on at the moment. I've got 
two shades, one is great for the Summertime for

me and the other one is just a little bit too 
light possibly now but the shade I wanted was

out of stock so we'll just make do. First of 
all I want to show you how it actually looks.

That's kind of like one pump and I'm using my 
Real Techniques Expert Face Brush to apply this

so I like to start in the middle actually of 
my face where I have the most pigmentation

and then work my way out, don't be afraid to apply 
it under your eyes and use it as a concealer.

I still have a fair amount left on my hand 
and let's bring you in a bit closer and see,

that it's a pretty good coverage so this is a 
medium coverage foundation but you can build it

up to full coverage. It doesn't feel heavy on the 
skin, it still needs a bit more time to dry down

still a little bit tacky. And because this can be 
used as a concealer as well it's perfectly fine to

apply under the eye. What I'm doing is I'm patting 
- stippling actually the brush and the foundation

into my skin rather than buffing around because 
I don't want to get brush marks, not that this

brush leaves many brush marks but stippling it 
pressing it into the skin especially on the areas

that need more coverage. I'm going to go away 
now put the rest of my makeup on. I'm going to

do 2 check-ins so you can see how it's held up and 
then I'll give you my final findings and thoughts

on this and we'll conclude with whether or not 
I think that you should go ahead and try it.

Okay so up close and personal and you can see that 
it hasn't accentuated the lines under my eyes,

remember I didn't use any primer I just used 
skincare and it hasn't actually broken down after

5 hours and it hasn't accentuated any of my dry 
patches predominantly sort of around my mouth area

and nor has it accentuated my pores in fact they 
look quite minimised so really happy with this.

The finish is still very radiant without looking 
oily or greasy which i'm really pleased about.

The consistency is creamy it's rich but also 
it's lightweight so when you put it on your skin

you don't feel like it's heavy or cakey or too 
much you don't need a huge amount I used a pump

if you want more coverage it's 
buildable you can apply it with a sponge

or you can use a brush like I did. 
I feel that the sponge probably

doesn't give you as much coverage if you're 
after full coverage then go with a brush.

It hasn't broken down but you can definitely 
see shine on the skin and also on the sides of

my nose you can see where my glasses were and 
it has slightly rubbed off but nothing major.

All in all I think this stood up very well. It 
claims to be long wearing was it long wearing?

Well yeah I think for sure it was, I did a 5 hour 
check-in and then a 10-hour check-in and as far

as I'm concerned it still looked pretty amazing. 
It's creamy it's flawless it's lightweight did it

cover my imperfections? Yes it did with just 
one application around the middle of my face

which has pigmentation, it did a marvellous job, 
it felt smooth it felt flawless even without

setting it and also it's water resistant so 
that's a big positive especially um in the warmer

months - which seem so far away at the moment! But 
if you've got an oily skin I definitely recommend

a setting powder or using a primer first for oily 
skin or using a setting spray and I love this NYX

setting spray - again it's affordable 
makeup, it does the job really really well.

And back to the Milani 2 in 1 
Perfect and Conceal Foundation,

it hasn't got a huge price point, it comes in 29 
shades, it's cruelty free and although the formula

is rich and creamy it doesn't make your skin 
feel greasy or oily. When I weigh it up against

other foundations that I've got and use which cost 
maybe £10 £15 - £20 pounds more than this one,

I think why wouldn't I use this?! At the moment 
it is my Holy Grail affordable foundation.

Am I going to find something better? I hope 
so, I'm really excited to try lots of new

foundations and if there's one that you want me 
to try, drop it in the comments below! Always on

the lookout for amazing affordable foundations 
especially for dry mature skin and thank you to

all my lovely subscribers! Take care everyone 
I'll see you in the next video. Bye for now!

Q5rxLst37J4.title: [Series of the Month] Makeup tutorial w the products reviewed this month
Q5rxLst37J4.description:
Hey guys, it’s me Aego!

Today, I'll be taking some time to do my makeup with the products that Heiley and I’ve reviewed this month.
With the start of the new year, we also started this kind of fun content for the first time.

Hope you guys enjoy the video🙊❤

⏱TIME LINE⏱
00:00 - Greeting
00:14 - Skin care
01:53 - Base makeup
02:49 - Eye makeup
04:00 - Blush
04:31 - Lip makeup
05:01 - Side thought
05:20 - Closing

#makeuptutorial #skincare #dailymakeup

transcript_raw.text: Hey guys, it’s me Aego here, Hi
Hello.
Today, I'm gonna take some time to do my makeup with the products that Heiley and I’ve reviewed this month.
I’ll be using the products that I took a liking to as I was reviewing them.
So first I’ll start with the skin care.
For the skin care products, I’ve brought The Lab By Blanc Doux’s Oligo Hyaluronic Acid 5000 Toner
and HolikaHolika’s GOOD CERA Super Ceramide Cream which I had reviewed this month.
The Lab By Blanc doux’s Oligo Hyaluronic Acid 5000 Toner has watery a formulation,
with a light application and finish that I really liked.
While I also liked Tonymoly’s Wonder Ceramide Mochi Toner Pad,
since my skin is not extremely dry type,
The Lab By Blanc Doux’s product is moderately moist and suited me well.
Even when applying it on once more after having already wiping it along my skin texture once,
it doesn’t feel heavy at all, and just left my skin feeling moist.
If you want sufficient moisture from a toner,
I recommend applying it on in multiple layers after you wipe your skin with it once,
or use it as a toner pack before moving on to the next skin care product.
After tidying up the texture of my skin with the toner,
I’ll lightly moisturize my skin and then I’ll move on to apply a cream.
When I first tried using HolikaHolika’s GOOD CERA Super Ceramide Cream I had expected that it would feel stuffy and heavy,
but I took a real liking to it because of how light and moist it was.
Having oily dehydrated skin, the cream didn't feel stuffy for me, and I found it sufficiently light and moist for my skin.
It does get stuffy over time when I apply on too much, so I would only apply it in small amounts.
And since my cheeks feel a bit drier compared to other areas,
I would normally apply on one more layer.
I think this would be best for people with dry skin to apply on small amounts in layers than to put on a lot at once like me.
Like this, I’m done with my quick and simple skin care routine, and now I’ll move on to my base makeup.
Heiley Ssaem reviewed base products from two brands this month.
And among them, is a product from Hince.
Since I’ve been very curious about their products myself, I tried using the one from Hince.
I went with the one for No.24 shade.
I was really taken back with how light and moist this foundation was when I first tried it.
It feels like I’m applying on a lotion, and I can feel how it sticks tightly to my skin.
The foundation also seems to have a slightly semi-matte finish.
I used the brush that came with the Hince Foundation set to apply it on.
The combination with the brush seemed to be better than I expected, but it didn't seem to provide any coverage.
I think this is probably a foundation that’s just for creating beautiful and clean looking skin.
I usually use shade #23, but the #24 from Hince is said to be okay as well.
I used the brush to apply this foundation, but when I tried it with my fingers before,
I felt that it would get cakey if I were a bit heavy handed with my skin care.
So, if you are going to use this foundation, it would be good to keep this point in mind when using it.
Like this, after my base makeup, I will now move on to do the eye makeup.
For my eyes, I used Laka's New Level Eyeshadow Palette which was reviewed by Heiley Ssaem.
Of the three palettes in total, I used No. 3 Outlook.
I chose this palette because I tend to use brown colors most often.
I really like its composition of variable base, point, and glitter colors.
And the design is quite trendy and pretty.
First, as a base, I applied the 7th color Ginger, on to my eyelids and on the entire underline.
Next, I applied the slightly darker No.6 Deep Beige, on the eyelids and underline to give some shade.
Next, I applied No.5 Warm Brown from the corners of the eyes to add depth, and then apply a thin layer all over the underline.
Then, I lightly swept No.2 Ash Orange over my eyelids.
And after doing my eyeline and mascara,
I used a thin brush to apply No. 8 Shine Nude to the front of the eyes.
And next, I drew the eyebrow with the darkest color, No. 5 Warm Brown, to complete my eye makeup.
and I also used No.7 and No.6 to give some shading on the side of my nose.
Then I gave some highlighter with No.8.
Like this, after having done my eye makeup with the eyeshadows, and applied on my eyeliner, mascara, eyebrow, shading and highlighter, I'll apply on a blush.
I didn't review the blush products this month, but I used this product as a blusher since I thought it’s also good as a blusher.
I used Mos’s Air Matte Rouge Lipstick.

Although this is a matte lipstick, it has a moist application and good adhesion, so 
I think it would look pretty as a blush as well.
There are of a total of 8 colors that all seem to feel natural when applied lightly,
so I think you can easily choose and use the color you want.
I applied a bit of the lipstick on my ring finger,
then I started applying it to my cheekbones first.
I extended the range of the blush by tapping it out.
I applied it as if it’s going upwards to the temple area.
Now, as for my lips, I used Amuse's Dew Tint.
I used 2 colors of Amuse's Dew Tint. No.6 and No.12
I first applied a very thin layer of No.6 as my base
by making it look as if it was smeared in an over lip.
And then applied No.12 only on the inside of the lips to make them look plump and pretty.
And there you have it!
My [Series of the Month] makeup is done using the products we’ve reviewed this month.
We’ll be releasing a [Series of the Month] video every month with the release of our new content.
Since this is the first video of this series, I went ahead by using the products Heiley Ssaem and I reviewed this month.
With the start of the new year, we also started this kind of fun content for the first time.
I wonder what kind of content we’ll be seeing in the series of the month release next month.
So my video is till here,
Thank you for watching my video today🙏🏻
Don’t forget to subscribe▶️
Press the like buttons👍🏻
And please leave some comments for me💌
I’ll see you guys next time.
BYE BYE

The Lab By Blanc doux’s Oligo Hyaluronic Acid 5000 Toner has watery a formulation,
with a light application and finish that I really liked.
While I also liked Tonymoly’s Wonder Ceramide Mochi Toner Pad,
since my skin is not extremely dry type,
The Lab By Blanc Doux’s product is moderately moist and suited me well.
Even when applying it on once more after having already wiping it along my skin texture once,
it doesn’t feel heavy at all, and just left my skin feeling moist.
If you want sufficient moisture from a toner,
I recommend applying it on in multiple layers after you wipe your skin with it once,
or use it as a toner pack before moving on to the next skin care product.
After tidying up the texture of my skin with the toner,
I’ll lightly moisturize my skin and then I’ll move on to apply a cream.
When I first tried using HolikaHolika’s GOOD CERA Super Ceramide Cream I had expected that it would feel stuffy and heavy,
but I took a real liking to it because of how light and moist it was.
Having oily dehydrated skin, the cream didn't feel stuffy for me, and I found it sufficiently light and moist for my skin.
It does get stuffy over time when I apply on too much, so I would only apply it in small amounts.
And since my cheeks feel a bit drier compared to other areas,
I would normally apply on one more layer.
I think this would be best for people with dry skin to apply on small amounts in layers than to put on a lot at once like me.
Like this, I’m done with my quick and simple skin care routine, and now I’ll move on to my base makeup. 
Heiley Ssaem reviewed base products from two brands this month.
And among them, is a product from Hince.
Since I’ve been very curious about their products myself, I tried using the one from Hince.
I went with the one for No.24 shade.
I was really taken back with how light and moist this foundation was when I first tried it.
It feels like I’m applying on a lotion, and I can feel how it sticks tightly to my skin.
The foundation also seems to have a slightly semi-matte finish.
I used the brush that came with the Hince Foundation set to apply it on.
The combination with the brush seemed to be better than I expected, but it didn't seem to provide any coverage.
I think this is probably a foundation that’s just for creating beautiful and clean looking skin.
I usually use shade #23, but the #24 from Hince is said to be okay as well.
I used the brush to apply this foundation, but when I tried it with my fingers before,
I felt that it would get cakey if I were a bit heavy handed with my skin care.
So, if you are going to use this foundation, it would be good to keep this point in mind when using it.
Like this, after my base makeup, I will now move on to do the eye makeup.
For my eyes, I used Laka's New Level Eyeshadow Palette which was reviewed by Heiley Ssaem.
Of the three palettes in total, I used No. 3 Outlook.
I chose this palette because I tend to use brown colors most often.
I really like its composition of variable base, point, and glitter colors.
And the design is quite trendy and pretty.
First, as a base, I applied the 7th color Ginger, on to my eyelids and on the entire underline.
Next, I applied the slightly darker No.6 Deep Beige, on the eyelids and underline to give some shade.
Next, I applied No.5 Warm Brown from the corners of the eyes to add depth, and then apply a thin layer all over the underline. 
Then, I lightly swept No.2 Ash Orange over my eyelids. 
And after doing my eyeline and mascara,
I used a thin brush to apply No. 8 Shine Nude to the front of the eyes.
And next, I drew the eyebrow with the darkest color, No. 5 Warm Brown, to complete my eye makeup. 
and I also used No.7 and No.6 to give some shading on the side of my nose.
Then I gave some highlighter with No.8.
Like this, after having done my eye makeup with the eyeshadows, and applied on my eyeliner, mascara, eyebrow, shading and highlighter, I'll apply on a blush.
I didn't review the blush products this month, but I used this product as a blusher since I thought it’s also good as a blusher.
I used Mos’s Air Matte Rouge Lipstick.
Although this is a matte lipstick, it has a moist application and good adhesion, so 
I think it would look pretty as a blush as well.
There are of a total of 8 colors that all seem to feel natural when applied lightly,
so I think you can easily choose and use the color you want.
I applied a bit of the lipstick on my ring finger,
then I started applying it to my cheekbones first.
I extended the range of the blush by tapping it out.
I applied it as if it’s going upwards to the temple area.
Now, as for my lips, I used Amuse's Dew Tint.
I used 2 colors of Amuse's Dew Tint. No.6 and No.12
I first applied a very thin layer of No.6 as my base
by making it look as if it was smeared in an over lip.
And then applied No.12 only on the inside of the lips to make them look plump and pretty.
And there you have it!
My [Series of the Month] makeup is done using the products we’ve reviewed this month.
We’ll be releasing a [Series of the Month] video every month with the release of our new content. 
Since this is the first video of this series, I went ahead by using the products Heiley Ssaem and I reviewed this month.
With the start of the new year, we also started this kind of fun content for the first time.
I wonder what kind of content we’ll be seeing in the series of the month release next month.
So my video is till here,
Thank you for watching my video today🙏🏻
Don’t forget to subscribe▶️
Press the like buttons👍🏻
And please leave some comments for me💌
I’ll see you guys next time.

first_page_comments_list.comment:
Yay!! I love the RGB lights in the back!!! So happy to see you in my YT feed <3

*A suggestion you never asked for* If you are looking for a way to absorb sound reverb, try hanging tapestries/macrame art or choosing a fluffy rug for your area. Southern American houses commonly have tile floors which are terrible for sound. Soft fabrics will help absorb it! That's why sound studios often have foam or carpet on the walls.

Much Love <3
replies: OMG I watched more of the video and your audio got so much better. Idk if you used a different microphone, pop or what, but great change!!

first_page_comments_list.comment: Ugh that liner look is so gorgeous, but I can never do it because my eyes water so much. So happy so see Angie videos again! 🎊

I'm trying to do a low-buy this year, so I decided a maximum of 12 palettes this year, and I already have spots reserved for hypothetical palettes of my favourite brands so, between that and already having the Kaleidos Lunar Lavender y the Glamshop Moro I'm passing this one hahaha

Loving the lightning! Paired with the look

PS: what is going to happen now with BH? I'm shook
replies: @Amy -chan oh for sure! Keeping a running wishlist and waiting for a while to buy things has really helped me cut down my purchases. Don't get me wrong, there are still a couple of launches that I instantly jump on! But every now and then I re examine my list and, more often than not, will delete something, or sometimes catch a good sale. I had the Athr beauty blush trios on my list for like a year, and at $44 each, I couldn't justify that for blush. And just recently, I got them from their website for $10 each!!! If I'd have known they were final sale, I would have bought backups. I am obsessed and now they are gone 🥲

@PaceYourselfFitness thanks you! I find doing a kind of hypothetical wish list helps a lot because when I see a new release my head goes like "do I like this stuff so much that I would erase something of my list to buy this instead?"🤣🤣
@Lilly H thanks you a lot!💗 I'm hoping to do god as I have a good curated collection which I love!
@eimearinez same!! Like some of my hypothetical sales are for high end brands, so a woman has to save money with sales!
That is such a good idea! I am on a low buy until April and girl, my list just keeps getting longer 😅 I hope it goes well for you!!!

first_page_comments_list.comment: So happy you're back! Love how the background is purple like the palette, looks so cozy 😊

Can we talk about the talent and artistry that it takes to use mediocre products and still end up with an absolutely stunning look? The matte shades Angie used in the second look tried to fail, but she made it work in spite of that. So incredible.
I love the purple in the background 💜 look amazing.  I don't care what anyone says I love colorpop
I’m grateful for your pickiness with the amount that ColourPop releases; it definitely helps the rest of us navigate.

Your looks in this video are beautiful! Regarding your set up, the lighting for the second look is perfect, and the sound quality is much better in the first look.

Also, with Ulta it's worth opening their emails and/or getting the app because they often offer special multipliers for rewards points (ie 5x the points on a certain brand or category). They're the easiest way to build points quickly and get free stuff. The offers have to be activated, though. And only redeem your points in increments of 2000 because that's the maximum value per point (the more points you redeem at once the more they're worth).
replies: @Angelica Nyqvist The sound was just too low for the 2nd look you did. I could barely hear it even with my sound turned all the way up.  Maybe you can turn it up?  And I agree with another comment on here about Southern floors having tile so adding a rug helps a lot with echo.  Thx!

Oh, the hauls I have gotten from point multipliers on things I would have bought anyway!! I have scored big time. I buy at Ulta as much as I can for even everyday stuff like body wash and cotton swabs 😆  Very sound advice, love the app, only thing that stinks is not pics on the reviews
Oh I wont be going with that sound though, its too sharp and echo’y, Im surprised you like it more actually :)

first_page_comments_list.comment: Hi Angie. I’m so happy to have you back! I really love the new settings. Very vivid. I truly appreciate how much you care about your videos and how hard you work to make them so fantastic. Forever subscriber!

Both colour settings were so incredibly pleasing to watch! The cool lavender light in the background, the lavender eyeshadow, light green nails, deep green leaves, even the colours from your top in the first half! Fantasticcc combinations. Your aesthetic and tastes are amazing but that’s no surprise!💜
replies: Thank you so much!

first_page_comments_list.comment: I appreciate that you are working hard to make the lighting and settings to make it true to life so much! Thank you for being you 😊

From this side of the camera, you and the eyeshadow look great, but then, you always look fantastic! As an older woman, I don’t mind having a “weaker” color. While I love the intensity of colors on someone your age and coloring, those intense colors can be overpowering on someone older. You always do a great job with color even when the palette is not up to your expectations.

Hey Angie! Good to have you back :) as you mentioned, I too have found that there are different colourpop formulas and levels of quality. I thought the Mandalorian and the Child were both lacklustre and dusty but Lush Life was a knockout. The Plush Like Me palette was somewhere in the middle.

For a company that is in charge of their own formula, production and quality control, i find it odd that there are so many complete misses when they’re also capable of such hits. Why so many variables and differences in quality when they literally own their own factory? Weird!

Either way, love the looks (and the eyeliner is fab on you)
WELCOME TO THE U.S. ANGIE! SO EXCITED TO HEAR YOU SAY "I BOUGHT IT AT ULTA" 🥰

OOOHHHH that first look is so stunning! I love the muted tones, and the eyeliner/lashes makes it so dramatic! That is definitely a perfect example of a "wearable" look for work or running errands during the day, then just put on the dramatic liner and lashes to go out for the evening. Gorgeous and so practical!
