first_page_comments_list.comment: I stopped buying drug store when I became more skilled in makeup. As a black woman, the shade ranges and undertones just weren't there. Although shade ranges have come along way, there is still room for improvement in the drug store. With that being said, I purchased the L'Oreal skin tint serum which was my first drug store purchase in years. I also dont like drug store eyeshadows because the quality isnt there - this includes Colourpop for me. I also recognized drug duping just lead me spend more vs spending the money on what I really wanted and being 100% satisfied. Idk, im trying to get into drug store more now that my collection is 95% where I want it to be.
replies:
I definitely agree. I live in Germany and the shade range in the drugstore is even worse here than the US. If I want base products, I can only buy them online, because they don't carry our shades in-store and opened makeup is non-refundable. So I just don't bother with it anymore. They used to have them. Maybelline once discontinued the FitMe shades after 335 here and only brought them back after backlash and petitions.

At least stores like Sephora or Douglas have mid-range to high-end brands with decent shade ranges to try out in-store. Also, a lot of drugstore brands feel like the fast fashion of makeup like Colourpop.
I dealt with the same thing there isn’t a lot of options for black people or people in color in general and I started using mid range to high end because if this

I am also a black woman and agree about the shade range. I also feel like drug store foundations never really catered to people with oily skin either so even if they did have my shade, i wouldn't work for me anyways.

@Tash the one dupe that has been fantastic is the ccolor  dupe for Born to Run. I have both and actually like the dupe better. It’s easier to travel with, too. But every other dupe I’ve tried is garbage so I’ve stopped trying. So many wasted resources and unnecessary, unsustainable waste. I’d rather have quality than volume.

I tried to like CP but their glitters are garbage and get all over everything. I depotted all of them and 6 palette pack whittled to 3. 3 I never use. I feel like I totally wasted $60 on them when I could have just bought one higher end palette that I love and use. People scoff at $130 for ND or PMG but I’d rather have one really good useable palette than a bunch of mediocre ones that don’t work for me.

first_page_comments_list.comment:
Lauren, the fact you acknowledge your privilege and use your platform to promote inclusive brands constantly makes me so happy and just proud that I support someone like you.
I love loreal foundations, Rimmel London lip liners, and Maybelline powders as well.

Elf is truly That Bitch to be quite honest, almost every product from them is a BANGER and they are cruelty free and vegan ON TOP of being super affordable. They recently launched No Budge shadow sticks which you may like as primers, having tried the 4 pack holiday set I can say they are TRULY no budge but the shimmers and metallics are more of a suggestion than anything (fine for primer use imo). They do possibly play up texture or scaliness so YMMV. They also had a mini putty primer 3 pack for holiday that would probably be good for trying, their Poreless Putty Primer is a cult favourite and they also have Matte and Luminous options if you prefer that. It's just such a great brand! Surprised you don't have much from them, definitely a great place to start on a drug store journey.
replies: I love elf, but I do find their products hit or miss.  The hits truly are banger, but the misses...oof.  For example, for the waterline, the shadowsticks are my go to.  They truly do not budge.  Their eyeliner is a hard pass.  I can make the liner work if I set it with powder, but who wants to do that?  The cheek products skew fair.  I am a light/medium and I find I have to buy their darker shades to work on my skin.  Props to elf's website.  I can only get a limited amount of products from my small town drugstore.  $15 to get free shipping and wicked good gifts/sales makes the website a go to for me.

I'm convinced the eyeshadow sticks are a reformulation or remake of the smudge pots that got discontinued LMAO those things did NOT budge or move at all, and neither do the shadow sticks. I used to wear the smudge pots 14+ hours with no problem and can do the same with the new shadow sticks
yesss love elf and their putty primer!! their mint melt primer is amazing too, i’ve heard people say it’s a dupe for the milk hydro grip
The elf ultra precise brow pencil is the only brow pencil I will use as long as it exists.
I really like the elf shadow sticks. I use them more often as liners, but they work well for me.

first_page_comments_list.comment: My collection is a mix of drugstore and mid-range. If I can get a great price on a prestige brand, and it’s something I love and can get a lot of use out of— then it’s completely worth spending a little more than a drugstore product.
Love hearing your voice and just watching feels like talking to a good friend!
for affordable highlight, try the catrice ones with the flower imprint! they are amaaaazing
replies: The More Than Glow Highlighters! Beyond Golden Glow (gold) and Supreme Rose Beam (icy pink). They are very nice. 🌟

first_page_comments_list.comment: One drug store foundation I really enjoy is the Loreal Infallible Pro Glow...and it's $5.48 on Amazon right now.  For a lighter coverage, the Wet and Wild Moisturizing Hydrator (?) is a great pick for around $5 and offers a light coverage that I enjoy for every day wear.  I am 54, with very few skin imperfections, and both work great for me.
replies: I second that! I'm 26 and have really bad hormonal acne, and the Infallible Pro Glow also has really good buildable coverage if you need it too!
Oooh I second the wet n wild tinted hydrator bought it on Amazon for 3.50!!! Lol I was godsmacked, loved it

first_page_comments_list.comment:
Jcat chrome shadows have been in kathleenlights favorites for years. They are classic happy you finally got to try them
As for my recommendations : i loove

- the physician formula healthy foundation (LN3 is my perfect shade) and

- the physicians formula spotlight illuminating primer ( better than the Charlotte tilbury one)

- eye primer my fave would be the wet n wild eye primer (i used it for so many years)

- wet n wild blush in melon wine (brownish blush)

- wet n wild highlighter in blossom glow

For bronzer you should try the kiko stick one

I LOVE the drugstore so I do have some recommendations for you... (sorry in advance for the length of this comment lol)

Primers:
- wet n wild impossible (smoothing but silicone free)
- wet n wild glass correct (I have the green one for redness, but a good hydrating primer)
- elf mint melt (like the hydrogrip and cooling on the skin, makes my makeup LAST)

Concealer:
-NYX born to glow (my holy grail, creamy and blendable with a nice medium coverage)
-elf hydrating Camo concealer (creamy, high coverage, really nice all over the face as a lighter option rather than foundation)

Powder:
-elf halo glow setting powder (I use it as a finishing powder it looks so pretty over everything and airbrushes the complexion while giving it a healthy glow)

Brows:
-elf wow brow gel (fibrous brow gel but the spoolie is a really nice size and the consistency isn't too wet or dry)

Blush:
-burt's bees (I have bare peach but they come in beautiful shades and the finish is a natural satin)
- elf bite size duo (my personal favorite is spiced apple because it's a sunburn type color but they have a large variety and are priced insanely well)
-essence satin touch blushes (gorgeous shades and the finish is a skin like matte)

Bronzer:
-essence sun club matte bronzer (a really nice warm-toned bronzer that is matte without being flat on the skin)
-elf putty bronzer (comes in various shades and is super easy to blend, long lasting and looks natural)

Highlight:
-essence pure nude (a perfect natural glow that can be built up to be more intense, but also worn sheer to be more natural...I also sometimes use this with a fluffy brush all over the face as a finishing powder)

Mascara:
-loreal voluminous lash paradise (my holy grail mascara, super volumizing without getting too clumpy)
-loreal telescopic (lengthening and the wand is long and skinny so perfect for getting all your lashes, especially the bottom)
-elf big mood (volumizing and dramatic)

Eyeliner:
-NYX epic wear gel liners (come in beautiful colors, super creamy and long lasting in the waterline)

Lip Liner:
-milani understatement lipliners (gorgeous shades, creamy formula, long lasting)
-colourpop lippie pencils (same as above)

Lipstick:
-revlon lustrous mattes (comes in the most beautiful shades, formula is matte perfection it is comfortable and soft on the lips but long lasting and looks gorgeous)

Edit (I forgot setting spray oops)

Setting Spray:
-NYX Dewy setting spray (long lasting and doesn't make the skin too dewy but adds a healthy glow and helps to diffuse makeup)

if you read this whole thing you're a real one lmao
replies:
For mascara, Essence Princess Lash is also a great one
Bronzer and blush, Milani's baked bronzer and baked blush are fantastic
For eyeshadows, I don't really like palettes so I don't have any reccs, but Catrice's Liquid Metal eyeshadows are great one-pot options. As the name implies, they aren't mattes though
Catrice's lip stuff is also great; I particularly like the Matte Lip Artists, they're a creamy sort-of bullet-but-not-really type of lipstick. They look matte on the lips but aren't super drying, they're actually pretty comfy to wear. They're not super long lasting but you can get 4-6 hours of wear from them easy, which is usually enough for me
Wow, thanks for taking the time to share this list!

first_page_comments_list.comment: I use 90% drugstore/affordable makeup, and 10% indie brands as a treat when I can afford it. I really appreciate these type of videos.
You HAVE to get the Flower Beauty Heatwave Bronzer! Rivals Hourglass!!
Yes! I’m so glad you said the Jcat reminded you of Roen because I thought so too. And they have way more colors available and they are cheaper. But they are still so good!

Here are some recommendations from a poor slavic person: Essence mascara (I need a miracle, Double trouble, Princess mascaras), their primers (mattifying one is good), their serums are great as well as lip balms and liquid lipsticks and glosses are phenomenal, contouring duo is great too. From Revolution i recommend Hydrate & Fix setting spray, their reloaded blushes and bronzers. Nyx- sweet cheeks blush either matte Or shimmery they have beautiful shades, I also love Nyx tinted skin veil. As far as eyeshadow goes Essence has those 3,5€ palettes and Catrice has bigger ones that are good not great. I think makeup Obsession has great eyeshadow. As for liner 100% Catrice tattoo ink Or that Nyx one ink something they are basically the same.

"Sniff out like a little Truffle Pig, ok?!" LOL, dying! Let's hope we can all live our best Truffle Pig lives on our makeup hunts this year! I feel like that every time I venture into drugstore. Many misses have been found, but when you do find that total gem of a product it's such a jolt of excitement! Thanks for making me giggle :D
Try the Nyx Marshmallow primer. ❤️ It’s so good. And Ulta sells a smaller size if you don’t want to commit to the big one.
replies: I think you can use Ulta coupons towards it. I agree that it’s on the pricier side for drug store.

I can't believe the price of that primer. It seems I could just grab NYX off the shelf without choking at the price once I get to the register. It might be reasonably priced for how amazing it might be but I won't know unless it goes on a massive sale.

first_page_comments_list.comment: Best drugstore primer: the impossible primer by wet ‘n wild. It’s a silicone-y primer without the silicone, but works well with all the foundations I have tried out with it so far.
I haven’t personally tried them, but I’ve heard revolution has a good shade range in some of their bronzer lines 😁😁

Hi! I love these drugstore videos and I'm bookmarking this one as there are tons of useful comments for me! Thank you all! (Btw, I find those Essence minipalettes very nice and I envy those who managed to buy the taupe and the coral one... I couldn't find them anywhere in stores - Italy - or on EU online stores!)
replies: @Layla yes, it helps :D no more envy xD

I picked up the Essence Taupe palette, if it helps at all, I would not really recommend it. I absolutely love the color story, but the shades apply lighter than they look in the pan. It's a bit hard to get much depth with it. I'm fair and it's a bit too light for me. I hope that helps.

first_page_comments_list.comment: I personally love the Milani lipliners.
replies: I love it more than the Charlotte tilbury liners

first_page_comments_list.comment: I’m organizing and moving my makeup downstairs and I just realized about an hr ago that I don’t own ANY drugstore makeup. WHEN did THAT happen like I feel like that’s something I should have noticed.

first_page_comments_list.comment: I will never understand how Pat McGrath and Natasha Denona have normalized $130, $150 eyeshadow palettes. I remember when people considered Naked palette's highend at $54, but now they're midrange? I just can't wrap my head around it
replies: @Manners Bananers A lot of people can afford Pat McGrath and Natasha Denona but think it is a little crazy to spend that kind of money for eyeshadow. Especially Natasha Denona. Beautiful color stories. Quality just average. To point it out isn’t jealousy or resentment. I think all luxury is BS. There is a point where the price far exceeds the quality. The more social media pushes these things the more people who go into hock to attain it the more other companies will see how far consumers will go and sell for higher prices.

They're luxury brands, just like Dior or Chanel. It's not "normalized", everyone knows that is a ridiculous price tag. It's like spending 1000$ on a handbag or a pair of shoes, or 100,000$ on a car. You don't do that because it's a normal price, you do that for yourself because it makes you feel very fancy and like you accomplished to be able to afford that. No one says you have to pay that price for an eyeshadow palette, there are plenty of fantastic brands with regular prices for you to choose from.
Well the people who got richer the last almost three years while average Americans were just trying to put meat on the table are helping line their pockets!
GREED!! PURE GREED!!
It's the Overton Window of makeup marketing 😂

first_page_comments_list.comment: I bought the collection at launch, despite the fact that the last big brand collab she did (Star Wars) left a bad taste in my mouth. Then I saw Theresa from Theresa is Dead review it and I started to feel turned off. It took forever to get here and when I checked their return policy it said it was 30 days from date of PURCHASE, and it took so long to get to me that I wouldn't have time to decide if I liked it or not before I'd have to return it. All the reviews I could find were from Pat McGrath fangirls so I didn't feel comfortable trusting them. What it finally came down to was it being $200+ for the whole collection and I didn't think I was going to enjoy it $200+ worth when half of what drew me in was the packaging, and I didn't like the packaging as much in person. I finally decided to return it all untried to save myself an expensive disappointment. I hope people who got it enjoy it but I decided it wasn't for me.
replies: Setting the return deadline based on date of purchase is shady af, especially from a luxury brand. The delays might be due to the panini situation but that's been going on long enough for PML to change their policy. At the very least it should be from date of shipping out, which is still questionable but I get that it's easier to trace than when it gets delivered to each and every customer.

first_page_comments_list.comment: Angelica, I have always really enjoyed your videos. I am also from Europe but have been living in States for a while now. Let me make a prediction, I think you are going to have 200 000 subscribers for Christmas 2022.

I've ordered from the Pat McGrath website twice, and both times it took almost two weeks to ship out.  Unless it's something that I can't get elsewhere, or there is some sort of crazy sale, I wait until it hits Sephora to order it.  I'm not sure why Pat McGrath gets so many passes for poor customer experience - a lot of other brands would be getting roasted for this!
I'm psyched about season 2! Season 2 is Anthony's story! I think my fave is Eloise's book, tbh.

I LOVE Bridgerton and loved this collection as well. I’ve read all of Julia Quinn and I agree the show is definitely going different! I am so excited for the new season in March!! I think season 2 the main love story will still be Anthony and I hope they end it with the masquerade ball to introduce Benedict’s story(my fav!). I think the beginning of Francesca’s story will need to occur Season 2 or Season 3. But because I haven’t seen much on casting I am not sure. I think there will definitely be some siblings overlapped love stories in Season 3 and 4!

I also read the books. I am excited to see what follows the same story and what is different. I like how they interpreted stuff for the first season. The Viscount Who Loved Me (Anthony’s story) was my fave. I need to read them again for sure. 🥰

You asked for my favorite book and I would say Gregory and then Francesca. I shocked my students this week when I told them I read them all in about a week, one a day. They took about 4 hours each 😍. I love hearing you talk about the series because I don't have anyone to talk about them with!

But if you want to read the Bridgerton series again I can recommend listening to them as audiobooks!
My favourite of the books is definitely Francesca as well! I love how different it is from the others, how secure she is in herself and how she doesn't just accept a man because she has to. My belief is that the Whistledown storyline will be included in season two as well as Anthony's storyline. I honestly kinda hope they leave out Eloise's storyline all over, because I feel like she changes drastically from the previous books in that one and it doesn't make sense with the Eloise we have gotten to know in the TV series. Eloise's arc also doesn't really make that much sense if the whole Wistledown reveal happens before it does in the books, but who knows really? Book 4, 5 and 6 happen almost simultaneously so they have a lot to play around with storywise.

first_page_comments_list.comment: Nomad's colour stories are bomb, this, the Halloween one, Iceland, and the Parks one? All gorgeous
Can I just say, our girl moved across a literal ocean and only took a rest for a short time and is BACK AT IT. We love you Angie! 😭

The National Parks palette blew me away, not just with the shades and the quality but with the packaging and presentation. It’s indie makeup but with bougie, boutique treatment of its customers 🙂 This new palette looks too cool-toned for me but I’m tempted to get it anyway because I want to support them.
replies: I was tempted to buy this and also wanted to support the brand but i realised i can dupe the vibes very easily from the palettes i already own and i also recently bought a few juvias place quad so i want to enjoy them before a made a new purchase
@LC I have Tokyo, Iceland & Berlin! Americas parks & haunted Europe are on my list
The national park, haunted euro and Iceland is on my list to buy. I already have Berlin, Tokyo and Marrakech that I bought 2 years ago.
@Glitter50 I’m on a total no-buy for a month! So yeah, same.
I want to support them also. I'm trying to not buy any makeup for a long time but.....

first_page_comments_list.comment: I love that it's NOT limited edition. I was supposed to be on a no-buy in January (except that I panic bought a bh cosmetics palette ahem) and a low-buy until summer and I'm not feeling like committing to a transatlantic order during a low-buy. I might pull the trigger down the line, as it is very beautiful!
replies: I cant believe BH is going bankrupt. I love BH! Their Sweet Shoppe collection are some of my all time fave palettes

@Lisa Moss I actually had two bh palettes that I wanted to buy come February, but Smitten in Switzerland sold out from BeautyBay a day or two after I put it on my wishlist, and it was also sold out from the German site, and on the US site it's nowhere to be found. Bh Germany said they're not restocking it as it looks now (I guess they can't afford it...). I'm really beating myself up over not getting it from BeautyBay when I had the chance ... but I don't currently have an income. But after Smitten in Switzerland disappeared from the face of the earth I panic bought Summer in St Tropez. Not letting it slip out of my reach!!!
I "panic bought" a BH Cosmetics palette too!

first_page_comments_list.comment: I love the new sound. It's less echoy and more clear. And these two look! Especially the second one, so so pretty. You never disappoint with colorful eye looks! Love it!
replies: @VioletteOrdinaire I agree. For me, the new sound comes off muffled. Like the new light settings though 🙂
My laptop absolutely hates the new sound setting. It sounds muffled and I heard static noises.

first_page_comments_list.comment: Nomad is just fantastic! The quality is amazing! This color story / just spot on! Simply stunning. Will use your code when I order! ❤️❤️
replies: @Angelica Nyqvist BTW a happy Birthday Doll!
Thank you Virginia! ❤

first_page_comments_list.comment: Nomad's colour stories are right up my alley. I own three palettes from them now (Orient Express, Iceland Fire&Ice and Haunted Europe) and they're all so good! Definitely gonna get this one, it's similar to the Wilderness palette by BeautyBay, but icier and without the shades I personally don't care for.

I need to work more with the Nomad palettes I have because I don't know that I always love their formulas? But I maybe just haven't spent enough time with them. You made me want this palette! It's so gorgeous with the packaging and the color story, and your looks were inspiring
replies:
I am not a fan of their mattes, at all. Or, at least their older mattes, anyway. They do NOT build on each other. You can absolutely do a "one matte crease and a shimmer on the lid" kind of look, but anything slightly more complex, and they tend to become VERY difficult to work with.

It's like they're too finely milled and powdery to stick to each other, or something? It's bizarre.

I haven't tried any of their newer mattes, though. I disliked the mattes so much that I don't really want to take another chance.

first_page_comments_list.comment: I am definitely getting this palette!! The first one I bought was Haunted Europa and I love it and this is another stunning palette!! Love your new background/home from what I’m seeing!! I have to catch up on your videos since you arrived in the US lol!
Haunted Europe is the most beautiful and unique themed eyeshadow palette. Imo, Nomad keeps getting better and better!!!! Thank you for doing these 2 looks… i need some inspiration 💙💙💙💙

I love Nomad cosmetics.  I'm trying to talk myself out of new releases this year and have a low buy year......not sure it's going to go over real well when Nomad keeps making the most beautiful things.

I love how the second eye look came out 🥰 they were both gorgeous looks. Your sound and settings definitely improved with the second eye look as well. I always love the personal touches that come with Nomad orders. And yay for an affiliate code!
When you put that blue shimmer on the first look- wow. The second look was very pretty the way you did it. Very spring. Couldn’t hear any background besides some video type sound at end.

That 2nd look is so beautiful and unique, I went think to put those colors together and when you 1st started applying that brick red I was like Angie what are you doing, but in the end it's stunning and I want to recreate it
I knew that it would be great seeing you do looks with this palette because it looks very pretty!! Love the blue eye look 😍💙✨
Beautiful palette and stunning eye look! Hope you had an amazing birthday yesterday 🎂🎉💐 Mine is Wednesday, will be turning a bit older than 38 unfortunately 😜
Love the look. The sound,  background and settings looks excellent 👌.  Love ❤️ you  and your I your honest reviews
That second eyelook is absolutely amazing! I never would have thought that colour combo would be that good🤩
LOVE LOVE LOVE the background with all the green plants and decor 😍
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, Angelica!!! Thank you for all the great vibes, amazing artistry, and love you share with us! May all your dreams come true! 💖🥳💖

Ahoy, ahoy my name is lenka Oshry, welcome to Skincare 
with Lenka, before we start i would love if you

subscribe to my channel i will appreciate it a 
lot, in today's video i will review two Lelive

products specifically vitamin c serum and their 
tinted spf moisturizer, i have already reviewed

these items in my previous lelive review video 
but this time i have purchased the product and i

have been using them for a while so i can give you 
better review based on personal experience as well

Lelive is vegan, cruelty free, sulfate free, 
paraben free, dye free and they have conscious

packaging but they're not all fragrance free some 
of their products contain natural fragrances aka

essential oils, all right so let's start with the 
vitamin c serum and it's it's called: all glowed up

vitamin c turmeric plus hyaluronic acid brightening 
serum, i've been using this serum for a few

weeks i love it, i feel that it really improved 
my skin, the combination of the ingredients are

stunning, the packaging is studying, they don't 
use glass they use aluminium so you can

recycle those as well, the only plastic bit is the 
part of the dropper, this serum is fragrance

free so it doesn't have any natural or synthetic 
fragrance in it, the texture is really nice

i almost finished it up and then i realized 
i haven't reviewed it, you can see this nice yellow

color and it is a little bit jelly but not too 
much, absorbs really quickly, it's just really

good serum so let's talk about the ingredients 
in this serum, first one a very good one of

course it's niacinamide vitamin b3 and vitamin 
b3 is a antioxidant it reduces the oilness on the

skin, brightens the skin, reduce the redness, it is 
overall ingredient for all skin types no matter if

you have rosacea, if you have dry skin, if you have 
oily skin, if you have whatever skin niacinamide

is always good so this ingredient provides 
the brightness and in this serum of course

the next brightening ingredient in this serum is 
licorice root and licorice root is a antioxidant

it also reduces the redness, it is 
anti-inflammatory and fights hyperpigmentation

next ingredient in this serum is bakuchiol and 
bakuchiol is a antioxidant, it is anti-inflammatory

and antibacterial, it can improve hyperpigmentation, 
fine lines , wrinkle, skin texture and skin tone

it also contains salix alba or willow bark and 
willow bark is anti-inflammatory and antibacterial

of course it contains hyaluronic acid and hyaluronic
acid is humectant so it hydrates the skin by

capturing the water and push it into deeper 
layers of our skin and what about the vitamin

c and turmeric in this serum, well i don't think 
they do much because vitamin c or ascorbic acid

is super finicky, very hard to formulate 
it degrades easily, it oxidizes easily

and for vitamin c to be stable it needs to be 
formulated with vitamin e and with ferulic acid

so the serum contains vitamin e but is missing 
ferulic acid and also it needs to be at least

10% of ascorbic acid for it to have any 
effect on our skin and in this serum we don't know

how much vitamin c the percentage because they 
didn't state it, the last ingredient i will

mention in this serum is turmeric and turmeric 
is likewise very difficult ingredient because

of its ph and its water solubility, it has very 
very hard time to penetrate the skin membrane

...the cell membrane and do what 
it's supposed to do so again it

might do something and probably doesn't do 
anything in the serum but as i said before

this serum is amazing it's still going to give you 
glow up as i said i think it did improve my skin

i really like it and i will 
definitely purchase it again

and the next favorite product from lelive 
is their tinted spf moisturizer and this

is: all the shade marula tinted 
spf 30 broad spectrum moisturizer

this moisturizer it is sunscreen basically 
but in a form of moisturizer, so sunscreens

and moisturizer with spf they're basically 
the same thing but if this labeled  moisturizer

is probably more hydrating, more moisturizing, 
more nourishing for the skin, i have been using

this sunscreen for a while and i actually 
wearing it now instead of makeup foundation

my skin is clear so i don't 
have need to put full coverage foundation

i only want something to give me nice 
healthy glow and this indeed gives you

juicy skin, hydrated skin, the the shade is 
amazing even though it's much darker than my skin

when you apply it sort of disappear and just give 
you this fantastic glow and it is suitable for all

skin tones, the sunscreen ingredient in this 
sunscreen or moisturizer is zinc oxide and iron

oxides, iron oxide it gives the tint, the 
color of the the moisturizer and also protects

from a visible blue light and blue visible 
light is responsible for a hyperpigmentation

if you are darker skin tone and you are
battling  with hyperpigmentation this

spf might be just perfect for you and it 
is also mineral sunscreen so it's much gentler
than chemical sunscreen but make no mistake, chemical sunscreen and mineral sunscreen

they are equal good so use whatever is best for your 
skin, whatever feels good on the skin then wear

that sunscreen, this sunscreen contains aloe 
vera, aloe vera soothing and anti-inflammatory

it contains glycerin and hyaluronic acid those 
are humectants so they will hydrate your skin

it contains a sweet almond oil which is 
very rich in vitamin e that is antioxidant

and also in three fatty omega acids... three omega 
fatty acids it, contains moringa seed oil that is

anti-inflammatory and it is antioxidant so it will 
help scavenge the free radicals and protect our

skin, this is stunning moisturizer with spf 
or tinted sunscreen, it is actually unisex so

no matter what your gender is you can 
wear it no problem, it's just really nice hydrating

and gives you proper protection and i absolutely 
love it and i will definitely purchase it again

that's all for today, thank you so much for 
watching, if you enjoy my video please give

it thumbs up, hit the notification bell 
so you can see all my future videos

and don't forget to subscribe it will mean 
a lot to me if you do. Cao see you next time!
